dom-speechsynthesis-cancel.name: cancel
dom-speechsynthesis-cancel.summary: The cancel() method of the SpeechSynthesis interface removes all utterances from the utterance queue.
dom-speechsynthesis-cancel.title: SpeechSynthesis.cancel()

dom-speechsynthesis-getvoices.name: getVoices
dom-speechsynthesis-getvoices.summary: The getVoices() method of the SpeechSynthesis interface returns a list of SpeechSynthesisVoice objects representing all the available voices on the current device.
dom-speechsynthesis-getvoices.title: SpeechSynthesis.getVoices()

dom-speechsynthesis-onvoiceschanged.name: onvoiceschanged
dom-speechsynthesis-onvoiceschanged.summary: The onvoiceschanged property of the SpeechSynthesis interface represents an event handler that will run when the list of SpeechSynthesisVoice objects that would be returned by the SpeechSynthesis.getVoices() method has changed (when the voiceschanged event fires.)
dom-speechsynthesis-onvoiceschanged.title: SpeechSynthesis.onvoiceschanged

dom-speechsynthesis-pause.name: pause
dom-speechsynthesis-pause.summary: The pause() method of the SpeechSynthesis interface puts the SpeechSynthesis object into a paused state.

chrome_android.notes: In Android, pause() ends the current utterance. pause() behaves the same as cancel().

firefox_android.notes: In Android, pause() ends the current utterance. pause() behaves the same as cancel().

dom-speechsynthesis-pause.title: SpeechSynthesis.pause()

dom-speechsynthesis-paused.name: paused
dom-speechsynthesis-paused.summary: The paused read-only property of the SpeechSynthesis interface is a Boolean that returns true if the SpeechSynthesis object is in a paused state, or false if not.
dom-speechsynthesis-paused.title: SpeechSynthesis.paused

dom-speechsynthesis-pending.name: pending
dom-speechsynthesis-pending.summary: The pending read-only property of the SpeechSynthesis interface is a Boolean that returns true if the utterance queue contains as-yet-unspoken utterances.
dom-speechsynthesis-pending.title: SpeechSynthesis.pending

dom-speechsynthesis-resume.name: resume
dom-speechsynthesis-resume.summary: The resume() method of the SpeechSynthesis interface puts the SpeechSynthesis object into a non-paused state: resumes it if it was already paused.
dom-speechsynthesis-resume.title: SpeechSynthesis.resume()

dom-speechsynthesis-speak.name: speak
dom-speechsynthesis-speak.summary: The speak() method of the SpeechSynthesis interface adds an utterance to the utterance queue; it will be spoken when any other utterances queued before it have been spoken.
dom-speechsynthesis-speak.title: SpeechSynthesis.speak()

dom-speechsynthesis-speaking.name: speaking
dom-speechsynthesis-speaking.summary: The speaking read-only property of the SpeechSynthesis interface is a Boolean that returns true if an utterance is currently in the process of being spoken — even if SpeechSynthesis is in a paused state.
dom-speechsynthesis-speaking.title: SpeechSynthesis.speaking

tts-events.name: voiceschanged_event
tts-events.summary: The voiceschanged event of the Web Speech API is fired when the list of SpeechSynthesisVoice objects that would be returned by the SpeechSynthesis.getVoices() method has changed (when the voiceschanged event fires.)
tts-events.title: SpeechSynthesis: voiceschanged event

tts-section.name: SpeechSynthesis
tts-section.summary: The SpeechSynthesis interface of the Web Speech API is the controller interface for the speech service; this can be used to retrieve information about the synthesis voices available on the device, start and pause speech, and other commands besides.
tts-section.title: SpeechSynthesis

tts-section.name: SpeechSynthesisUtterance
tts-section.summary: The SpeechSynthesisUtterance interface of the Web Speech API represents a speech request. It contains the content the speech service should read and information about how to read it (e.g. language, pitch and volume.)
tts-section.title: SpeechSynthesisUtterance

tts-section.name: speechSynthesis
tts-section.summary: The speechSynthesis read-only property of the Window object returns a SpeechSynthesis object, which is the entry point into using Web Speech API speech synthesis functionality.
tts-section.title: Window.speechSynthesis

dom-speechsynthesiserrorevent-error.name: error
dom-speechsynthesiserrorevent-error.summary: The error property of the SpeechSynthesisErrorEvent interface returns an error code indicating what has gone wrong with a speech synthesis attempt.
dom-speechsynthesiserrorevent-error.title: SpeechSynthesisErrorEvent.error

speechsynthesiserrorevent.name: SpeechSynthesisErrorEvent
speechsynthesiserrorevent.summary: The SpeechSynthesisErrorEvent interface of the Web Speech API contains information about any errors that occur while processing SpeechSynthesisUtterance objects in the speech service.
speechsynthesiserrorevent.title: SpeechSynthesisErrorEvent

dom-speechsynthesisevent-charindex.name: charIndex
dom-speechsynthesisevent-charindex.summary: The charIndex read-only property of the SpeechSynthesisUtterance interface returns the index position of the character in the SpeechSynthesisUtterance.text that was being spoken when the event was triggered.
dom-speechsynthesisevent-charindex.title: SpeechSynthesisEvent.charIndex

dom-speechsynthesisevent-elapsedtime.name: elapsedTime
dom-speechsynthesisevent-elapsedtime.summary: The elapsedTime read-only property of the SpeechSynthesisUtterance interface returns the elapsed time in seconds after the SpeechSynthesisUtterance.text started being spoken that the event was triggered at.
dom-speechsynthesisevent-elapsedtime.title: SpeechSynthesisEvent.elapsedTime

dom-speechsynthesisevent-name.name: name
dom-speechsynthesisevent-name.summary: The name read-only property of the SpeechSynthesisUtterance interface returns the name associated with certain types of events occuring as the SpeechSynthesisUtterance.text is being spoken: the name of the SSML marker reached in the case of a mark event, or the type of boundary reached in the case of a boundary event.
dom-speechsynthesisevent-name.title: SpeechSynthesisEvent.name

dom-speechsynthesisevent-utterance.name: utterance
dom-speechsynthesisevent-utterance.summary: The utterance read-only property of the SpeechSynthesisUtterance interface returns the SpeechSynthesisUtterance instance that the event was triggered on.
dom-speechsynthesisevent-utterance.title: SpeechSynthesisEvent.utterance

speechsynthesisevent.name: SpeechSynthesisEvent
speechsynthesisevent.summary: The SpeechSynthesisEvent interface of the Web Speech API contains information about the current state of SpeechSynthesisUtterance objects that have been processed in the speech service.
speechsynthesisevent.title: SpeechSynthesisEvent

dom-speechsynthesisutterance-speechsynth.name: SpeechSynthesisUtterance
dom-speechsynthesisutterance-speechsynth.summary: The SpeechSynthesisUtterance() constructor of the SpeechSynthesisUtterance interface returns a new SpeechSynthesisUtterance object instance.
dom-speechsynthesisutterance-speechsynth.title: SpeechSynthesisUtterance.SpeechSynthesisUtterance()

utterance-events.name: resume_event
utterance-events.summary: The resume event of the Web Speech API SpeechSynthesisUtterance object is fired when a paused utterance is resumed.
utterance-events.title: SpeechSynthesisUtterance: resume event

utterance-events.name: start_event

utterance-events.title: SpeechSynthesisUtterance: start event

dom-speechsynthesisutterance-lang.name: lang
dom-speechsynthesisutterance-lang.summary: The lang property of the SpeechSynthesisUtterance interface gets and sets the language of the utterance.
dom-speechsynthesisutterance-lang.title: SpeechSynthesisUtterance.lang

dom-speechsynthesisutterance-onboundary.name: onboundary
dom-speechsynthesisutterance-onboundary.summary: The onboundary property of the SpeechSynthesisUtterance interface represents an event handler that will run when the spoken utterance reaches a word or sentence boundary (when the boundary event fires.)
dom-speechsynthesisutterance-onboundary.title: SpeechSynthesisUtterance.onboundary

dom-speechsynthesisutterance-onend.name: onend
dom-speechsynthesisutterance-onend.summary: The onend property of the SpeechSynthesisUtterance interface represents an event handler that will run when the utterance has finished being spoken (when the end event fires.)
dom-speechsynthesisutterance-onend.title: SpeechSynthesisUtterance.onend

dom-speechsynthesisutterance-onerror.name: onerror
dom-speechsynthesisutterance-onerror.summary: The onerror property of the SpeechSynthesisUtterance interface represents an event handler that will run when an error occurs that prevents the utterance from being succesfully spoken (when the error event fires.)
dom-speechsynthesisutterance-onerror.title: SpeechSynthesisUtterance.onerror

dom-speechsynthesisutterance-onmark.name: onmark
dom-speechsynthesisutterance-onmark.summary: The onmark property of the SpeechSynthesisUtterance interface represents an event handler that will run when the spoken utterance reaches a named SSML mark tag (when the mark event fires.)
dom-speechsynthesisutterance-onmark.title: SpeechSynthesisUtterance.onmark

dom-speechsynthesisutterance-onpause.name: onpause
dom-speechsynthesisutterance-onpause.summary: The onpause property of the SpeechSynthesisUtterance interface represents an event handler that will run when the utterance is paused part way through (when the pause event fires.)
dom-speechsynthesisutterance-onpause.title: SpeechSynthesisUtterance.onpause

dom-speechsynthesisutterance-onresume.name: onresume
dom-speechsynthesisutterance-onresume.summary: The onresume property of the SpeechSynthesisUtterance interface represents an event handler that will run when a paused utterance is resumed (when the resume event fires.)
dom-speechsynthesisutterance-onresume.title: SpeechSynthesisUtterance.onresume

dom-speechsynthesisutterance-onstart.name: onstart
dom-speechsynthesisutterance-onstart.summary: The onstart property of the SpeechSynthesisUtterance interface represents an event handler that will run when the utterance has begun to be spoken (when the start event fires.)
dom-speechsynthesisutterance-onstart.title: SpeechSynthesisUtterance.onstart

dom-speechsynthesisutterance-pitch.name: pitch
dom-speechsynthesisutterance-pitch.summary: The pitch property of the SpeechSynthesisUtterance interface gets and sets the pitch at which the utterance will be spoken at.
dom-speechsynthesisutterance-pitch.title: SpeechSynthesisUtterance.pitch

dom-speechsynthesisutterance-rate.name: rate
dom-speechsynthesisutterance-rate.summary: The rate property of the SpeechSynthesisUtterance interface gets and sets the speed at which the utterance will be spoken at.
dom-speechsynthesisutterance-rate.title: SpeechSynthesisUtterance.rate

dom-speechsynthesisutterance-text.name: text
dom-speechsynthesisutterance-text.summary: The text property of the SpeechSynthesisUtterance interface gets and sets the text that will be synthesised when the utterance is spoken.
dom-speechsynthesisutterance-text.title: SpeechSynthesisUtterance.text

dom-speechsynthesisutterance-voice.name: voice
dom-speechsynthesisutterance-voice.summary: The voice property of the SpeechSynthesisUtterance interface gets and sets the voice that will be used to speak the utterance.
dom-speechsynthesisutterance-voice.title: SpeechSynthesisUtterance.voice

dom-speechsynthesisutterance-volume.name: volume
dom-speechsynthesisutterance-volume.summary: The volume property of the SpeechSynthesisUtterance interface gets and sets the volume that the utterance will be spoken at.
dom-speechsynthesisutterance-volume.title: SpeechSynthesisUtterance.volume

dom-speechsynthesisvoice-default.name: default
dom-speechsynthesisvoice-default.summary: The default read-only property of the SpeechSynthesisVoice interface returns a Boolean indicating whether the voice is the default voice for the current app (true), or not (false.)
dom-speechsynthesisvoice-default.title: SpeechSynthesisVoice.default

dom-speechsynthesisvoice-lang.name: lang
dom-speechsynthesisvoice-lang.summary: The lang read-only property of the SpeechSynthesisVoice interface returns a BCP 47 language tag indicating the language of the voice.
dom-speechsynthesisvoice-lang.title: SpeechSynthesisVoice.lang

dom-speechsynthesisvoice-localservice.name: localService
dom-speechsynthesisvoice-localservice.summary: The localService read-only property of the SpeechSynthesisVoice interface returns a Boolean indicating whether the voice is supplied by a local speech synthesizer service (true), or a remote speech synthesizer service (false.)
dom-speechsynthesisvoice-localservice.title: SpeechSynthesisVoice.localService

dom-speechsynthesisvoice-name.name: name
dom-speechsynthesisvoice-name.summary: The name read-only property of the SpeechSynthesisVoice interface returns a human-readable name that represents the voice.
dom-speechsynthesisvoice-name.title: SpeechSynthesisVoice.name

dom-speechsynthesisvoice-voiceuri.name: voiceURI
dom-speechsynthesisvoice-voiceuri.summary: The voiceURI read-only property of the SpeechSynthesisVoice interface returns the type of URI and location of the speech synthesis service for this voice.
dom-speechsynthesisvoice-voiceuri.title: SpeechSynthesisVoice.voiceURI

speechsynthesisvoice.name: SpeechSynthesisVoice
speechsynthesisvoice.summary: The SpeechSynthesisVoice interface of the Web Speech API represents a voice that the system supports. Every SpeechSynthesisVoice has its own relative speech service including information about language, name and URI.
speechsynthesisvoice.title: SpeechSynthesisVoice
